ps6
Class PathDirections

java.lang.Object
  ps6.PathDirections
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<String>, Directions
public class PathDirections
extends Object
implements Directions

A PathDirections is a description of how to travel from one Address to another.

Specification Fields
  • start - : Address // starting point
  • end - : Address // destination
  • length - : double // traveling distance, in miles (not rounded)
  • route - : Route // this sequence of segments the directions // travel over
  • directions - : sequence[String] // directions for traveling from start to end. Each String in the sequence must be one line of directions, in the format specified in PS6 text based interface, excluding the first line which states where you start and the final line which gives the length/time of the trip. The strings must not include newlines at their ends. The order of the Strings in the sequence must correspond to the order of the lines in the directions from start to end.
